'''Beauclerk''' (first name and details of birth and death unknown) was an English [[cricket]]er with [[Amateur status in first-class cricket|probably amateur status]] who was active in 1831. He made his [[first-class cricket|first-class]] debut in 1831 and appeared in one match as an unknown [[handedness]] [[batting (cricket)|batsman]] whose [[bowling (cricket)|bowling style]] is unknown, playing in an A to K ''versus'' L to Z match organised by [[Marylebone Cricket Club]] (MCC). Possibly related to [[Lord Frederick Beauclerk]], he scored no [[run (cricket)|runs]] with a highest score of 0[[not out|*]] and took no [[wicket]]s.<ref name="CA36">{{cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/36/36338/36338.html |publisher=''CricketArchive'' |title=Beauclerk |accessdate=26 April 2014}}</ref>

